  "commit_full": "464c007ba65d000a3d8f7950f22f2fc9aa854b74",
  "commit_subject": "[SuperResolution] Port pretrained FSRCNN/ESPCN baseline weights (#27)",
  "commit_body": "Add src/convert_pretrained.py to remap yjn870's public FSRCNN (x2/x3/x4)\nand ESPCN (x3) PyTorch checkpoints onto our module structure, with\nstrict state-dict loading to catch shape/key mismatches. Commit the\nconverted weights to src/weights/.\n\nAlso fixes two issues found while validating the converted checkpoints:\n- SRModel used OpenCV's full-range YCrCb instead of the digital\n  video-range BT.601 Y'CbCr convention used by FSRCNN/ESPCN and most SR\n  literature, which measurably hurt PSNR.\n- Benchmarking a pretrained checkpoint with cv2-bicubic-generated LR\n  (as our own train/benchmark pipeline uses internally) makes it score\n  worse than bilinear, since the checkpoint was trained on PIL-bicubic\n  LR \u2014 a kernel-mismatch artifact, not a model defect. Documented in\n  docs/algorithm_readme.md and handled correctly in\n  convert_pretrained.py's verify_against_bilinear().\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
